Sean McQuade Final Deliverables: DACSS 690V

Intro

What are the characteristics the economic elite of the United States? This is the questions I aim to answer with my research team at the World Elite Database. Using a specific selection methodology (Young et al. (2024)), we construct a unique database containing a number of descriptive variables on the economic elite in the US. We combine these data with the Adam Bonica’s DIME Database (Bonica (2023)) to derive insights into the ideological patterns of individuals in our population.

The plots on this dashboard explore preliminary conclusions we can draw from our database so far.

References

Bonica, Adam. 2023. “Database on Ideology, Money in Politics, and Elections.” Stanford, CA: Stanford University Libraries. https://data.stanford.edu/dime.
Young, Kevin L, Jorge Q Velazco, Sean McQuade, and Shay O’Brien. 2024. “World Elite Database (WED) Methodological Report: Construction of the Economic Elite Population for the United States” 1.
